The paper involves the use of deep neural networks for assessing prostate biopsies, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of artificial intelligence (AI) methods also suggests the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also involves the evaluation of the performance of the AI, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the digitization of the biopsies and the use of deep neural networks suggest the use of deep learning (cs.DL) methods, which could also be a likely sub-category.
